article.headline: The Citadel 66, Webber 63
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. (AP) -- Demetrius Nelson scored 22 points and The Citadel rallied from 14-point deficit to beat Webber International 66-63 on Saturday. Webber International closed to 64-63 with 49 seconds remaining before Nelson hit two free throws with 25 seconds left to complete the scoring. Cameron Wells added 12 points and Matt Clark scored 11 points on 5-of-5 shooting for the Bulldogs (2-3), who shot 58.6 percent in the second half and rallied from a 31-21 halftime deficit. Halston Schaffer had 21 points and Alex Carmona added 11 for Webber International (4-6), which led 29-15 early before allowing the Bulldogs to rally. Guard Brandon Streeter was 0-for-11 from the field. Webber International committed 17 turnovers and made just 63 percent of its free throws.
